name: Diamond - Snake
description:
Snake - 7th of 10 art from the "Diamond Animals" collection.
In many ancient cultures, the snake was considered a sacred animal. She symbolized duality. On the one hand, snakes are cunning and insidious, and on the other, they serve as a standard of wisdom and the focus of knowledge. In 600 BC, the snake became a symbol of medicine, because its poison can kill or cure a person.
